To align a row of divs to the right, use the `flex-direction` property with value "row" and set its width attribute to 100%. Here's an example:

```css
.container {
display: flex;
}

.item1 {
width: 50%; /* or any other percentage */
/* Add your content here */
}

.item2 {
flex-direction: row;
width: 100% !important; /* Set the width to 100% for alignment */
/* Add your content here */
}
```
In this example, `.item1` will be centered horizontally and `.item2` will be aligned to the right of its parent container (`.container`). The `!important` attribute is used to ignore any width assigned by CSS for alignment purposes in order to align it perfectly to the right.
